  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What are Custom Directives?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Custom directives in Vue allow you to define reusable behavior that can be applied directly to DOM elements."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Why Use Custom Directives?"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Encapsulate DOM logic**",
        "**Reuse behavior across components**",
        "**Extend Vue functionality**",
        "**Handle low-level DOM operations**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Basic Example"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "app.directive('focus', {\n  mounted(el) {\n    el.focus();\n  }\n});"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Usage in Template"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<input v-focus>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Directive Hooks"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "value": {
        "headers": ["Hook", "Description"],
        "rows": [
          ["created", "Called before element is mounted"],
          ["beforeMount", "Before element is inserted"],
          ["mounted", "When element is inserted"],
          ["updated", "When component updates"],
          ["unmounted", "When element is removed"]
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "With Value"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "app.directive('color', {\n  mounted(el, binding) {\n    el.style.color = binding.value;\n  }\n});"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Usage with Value"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<p v-color=\"'red'\">Hello</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Best Practices"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Use directives only for DOM manipulation**",
        "**Keep logic simple and reusable**",
        "**Avoid business logic inside directives**",
        "**Use components instead when possible**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Common Mistakes"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Using directives instead of components unnecessarily**",
        "**Adding complex logic inside directives**",
        "**Not cleaning up in unmounted hook**",
        "**Misusing directive lifecycle hooks**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Conclusion"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Custom directives are useful for extending Vue functionality and handling direct DOM operations efficiently."
    }
  ],

  "faq": [
    {
      "question": "What is a custom directive?",
      "answer": "A reusable DOM behavior defined in Vue."
    },
    {
      "question": "When to use directives?",
      "answer": "For low-level DOM manipulation."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is binding.value?",
      "answer": "It contains the value passed to the directive."
    }
